The purpose of this study is to evaluate whether the introduction of large-scale telemonitoring of patients with COPD produces benefits in terms of improved health-related quality of life and reduced access to hospital facilities.

 In addition, the trial evaluates the economic and organisational impact of the new services, and examine their acceptability by patients and health professionals.

